text.section:
Subject to the hearing provisions of subsection (d) of this section, the Comptroller may suspend or revoke a license issued to a transient vendor under this subtitle if the transient vendor:
fails to notify the Comptroller as required under subsection (a) of this section;
provides false information to the Comptroller;
fails to collect the sales and use tax on all sales as required under Title 11 of the Tax - General Article; or
otherwise fails to comply with the provisions of the sales and use tax law or the provisions of this subtitle.
